column4: Diversity (Understanding Race, Ethnicity, and Gender) – DIVU4 Evaluate issues – Students will evaluate complex issues surrounding race, ethnicity, and/or gender in the context of their own beliefs, values, and attributes.
column11: Advanced: Demonstrate a sophisticated and multi-layered  ability to evaluate complex issues surrounding race,  ethnicity, and/or gender in the context of their own  beliefs, values, and attributes.
column13: Proficient: Demonstrate an advanced ability to evaluate complex issues surrounding race, ethnicity, and/ or gender in the context of their own beliefs, values, and attributes.
column15: Progressing: Demonstrate a basic ability to evaluate complex issues  surrounding race, ethnicity, and/or gender in the context of their own beliefs, values, and attributes.
column17: Beginning: Demonstrate a partial ability to evaluate complex issues surrounding race, ethnicity, and/or gender in the context of their own beliefs, values, and attributes.
column19: Unsatisfactory: Demonstrates little ability to evaluate complex  issues surrounding race, ethnicity, and/or gender  in the context of their own beliefs, values, and  attributes.
